Bit of a silly one, but a "last visited" statistic on each wiki page would be really useful for keeping wiki information up to date and relevant.  Something along the lines of \{last-visited:spaces=@ALL|reverse=true|total=20\} would show the 20 pages which haven't been visited for the longest time.  This could be put into some sort of system admin page/space/dashboard, and would allow administrators to find out which pages are no longer relevant or aren't being used, and be able to clean up or rectify as appropriate.

I don't believe that this is currently available in confluence (did a quick google and a search of this JIRA), so could be a nice future feature!

